<br>
Sirens Grotto<br>
<br>
A simple guide which will illustrate solutions to primary objectives of this zone.<br>
<br>
A few notes:<br>
This guide is written with the thought of using 1 solid group, not a several group raid.<br>
Seahorse, and fish see thru all types of invisibility.<br>
Other than named, all land based mobs, do not see thru invisibility.<br>
Any form of levitation does not work in this zone and it's considered a dungeon.<br>
Call of the Hero does work here.<br>
<br>
The first objective I'll explain is how to get from the Sirens Grotto/Cobalt Scar Zone line, to the Western Wastes zone line.<br>
Please look at this map *eqmaps.com*<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.wansecure.net/test/sgtoww.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <br>
There are only 3 mobs in the way which see thru all types of invisibility, they are all lvl 53 Seahorse.<br>
<br>
The method to get there, is to pull the first two, mez one, kill the other.  When it's dead, kill the 2nd one, and move up to kill the 3rd.  <br>
<br>
These cannot be snared or rooted, and they're pretty difficult to mez using Dazzle, although I'd recommend it if your cleric/healer can keep you alive thru a couple resists.<br>
<br>
One thing to note, is that if you get too many resists, or are low on mana and have aggro, just get out of the water on the ledge.<br>
<br>
Once the 3rd Seahorse is killed, invisi up and follow the path on the map. <br>
<br>
When you get to the &quot;0&quot; be careful as sometimes there is a Swordfish swimming around.<br>
<br>
Follow the red path invisible and you'll zone out to Western Wastes.<br>
<br>
<br>
The next objective is to get to the ramp area of sirens.  <br>
<br>
The reason for this is to get chest quest gems (Flawless Diamonds, Black Marble, and Pristine Emeralds)  <br>
<br>
There are a couple methods to getting there, I'll go over the one we use.<br>
Please reference this map *eqmaps.com*<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.wansecure.net/test/sg01.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <br>
You will need a swimming skill above 100 to ensure a death free passage.<br>
<br>
The first step, is to have an enchanter move to point &quot;1&quot; marked on the map, and target the first Seahorse.  Using Dazzle/GoK, mez this horse.  If you get a resist, then get out of the water, retarget, get in and try again until it's mez'd.<br>
<br>
After the first Seahorse is mez'd, move to point &quot;2&quot;, and Mez the 2nd Seahorse *Note: If mez doesn't hold, you can either get out of the water, or swim to the ledge along the path*<br>
<br>
You can kill them just as easy...although we don't bother.<br>
<br>
Once sitting on the ledge past the 2nd Seahorse, watch for the roaming Swordfish.  It will roam in a circle, sometimes changing directions.<br>
<br>
Once the Swordfish is on the far side, or heading in the opposite direction of you, jump into the water and swim following the path...the idea is to not get aggro on you until you're passing the two stationary sea horse.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.wansecure.net/test/sg02.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <br>
Do NOT stop swimming until you get to the area marked &quot;3&quot; on the map.  When you get to 3, be careful as there is a mob close...but you'll be able to see it.<br>
<br>
Once there, you will have lost aggro on the two Seahorse chasing you...we usually camp to clear aggro just to make sure.<br>
<br>
Once there, re-invis and move to point &quot;4&quot; on the map.  <br>
It should be noted that points &quot;3&quot; and &quot;4&quot;  and &quot;5&quot; are <br>
safe-ish camp spots.  <br>
<br>
Three mobs spawn just ahead of &quot;4&quot;, most of the time, they will not see thru invis.  <br>
<br>
I do NOT recommend pulling these.  <br>
Due to some serious pathing errors, it's more frustration than it's worth they will run all over, and you end up getting about 4 or so mobs all in one area and they won't pull...a real mess to deal with.<br>
<br>
Once at point &quot;5&quot; Have someone check down the hall to see if a mob that see's invisi is there.  If you have a monk, I'd recommend you getting aggro and training the mob along the green path on the map.  <br>
<br>
The mob will stay there and you will have a nice path without any mobs that see thru invis.<br>
<br>
If you do not have a monk or someone to FD the mob in that location, then you can move just to where the green path, separates from the red path, pause and recast invis, and move to point &quot;6&quot;.  <br>
<br>
Another method is to have an enchanter mez the Seahorse that typically spawns there, then invisi and go thru to the camp spot.  <br>
<br>
If you're unsure about the aggro, make sure you get to land, and camp to clear it.<br>
<br>
Due to pathing, you should have enough time to re-invis and move before getting hit.  <br>
<br>
*Note*<br>
If you get aggro with a land capable mob, then you will need to camp to lose aggro, or the pathing will eventually aggro a few land based mobs near your camp area, training you and killing your party.<br>
<br>
If you are not invisible and you get out of the water, prepare to fight at least two sirens.  At point &quot;6&quot; you are not in aggro range, and can CotH people in, or buff up.<br>
<br>
We usually invisi up to the top of the ramp...above the &quot;6&quot;.<br>
<br>
I'd recommend fighting from the top of the ramp down, as some mobs are enchanters and like to cast Gravity Flux, which will aggro everything in the room, causing either evac or wipeout.  We usually can clear the top tier, and 2nd tier before we get respawn.<br>
<br>
I'd not recommend doing Icy Servant other than if you're trying to get a wavecrasher mob spawn, and I'd recommend them solo (Due to AE dispell and DD)<br>
<br>
For a wavecrasher, if &quot;a shimmering sea spirit&quot; isn't wielding the WC then it doesn't have one.<br>
<br>
It should also be noted that high MR/CR is key here, as everything (ramp area) is a caster.<br>
<br>
If a mob gates, or drops off the ledge, evac and follow the above to start over...as a few sirens, a couple icy servants, and your party/raid will drop very swiftly.<br>
<br>
For every two tiers of clearing, we average one BP gem...or about 10 kills for a gem.  All drop about the same rate...meaning Melee, Priest, and Caster are just as common.<br>
<br>
