<br>
I should note also that I play on Test Server...so sometimes things may change, so I've only posted what I've also verified on a production server as well.<br>
<br>
Just past point 3, there is mob...the reason I said to reinvis is that chances are the two seahorse you had to swim by to get to that point, are going to have broken your invisi.<br>
<br>
The spawns there are random mob types, so it could be a mob that sees thru.  Although pathing really sucks there<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
We'd tried clearing them at first, and the mobs will get aggro and just run the other way, getting all their friends and pooling them together somewhere down the way...near where the green path starts...it's a real mess...so we just invisi past them.  If they see thru, you can almost always swim around them without getting aggro.  If you get aggro, I'd recommend getting to a safe spot and getting an invisi and camping to clear/reset the spawns.<br>
<br>
What we'll do is get to point 5, and get invisi and check the spawns, if there is a seahorse/fish where the green path spawn, someone will go around it...pathing is very bad in this area, and odds are the mob will just stand there...had aggro but can't path to you...<br>
<br>
If we can't pull the mob away...although we've always been either able to pull it away, or pull into the open area and kill, you can swim into the open area...along the red path after the green split, reinvisi there, and get out onto dry land.<br>
<br>
I should note that if you pull it into the open area...i.e. where the green pathing is...it's safe to fight there, but do NOT poke your head out of the water...or use pets...or you will aggro some Icy/Watery Servants, which will eat you for a snack.<br>
<br>
EB is required from point 1 until you get to point 6.<br>
<br>
Once you get to point 6, you'll be in an open room with some stone ramps that go up a few lvls.  We usually buff up at point 6 as you're out of aggro.  Once buffed, we get an invisi and head up the ramps until you're at point 6, but on the top most level.  <br>
<br>
From there we pull and kill...and start clearing the levels.<br>
<br>
As for group lvls, most of us were from 52 to 57 or so when going here... <br>
<br>
I think level would depend on how well your group works together.  <br>
<br>
I've done with with a 52 cleric, 54 enc, 52 mage, and 57 warrior...but I'd not recommend going in without snare/evac or some way to mez.<br>
<br>
There are more than enough spawns to keep a group busy there...and probably enough spawns to keep two groups busy...<br>
