<br>
We started the camp at the 4 &quot;white&quot; rooms at the very southern edge of the map.  Its alittle hard to explain but here goes...<br>
<br>
This are (4 rooms at southern edge of the map) is actually 2 tunnels connected by airpockets.  There is a water channel connecting all 4 rooms and another air channel above them connected at the 4 &quot;rooms&quot;.  The rooms are underwater and you can not move thru the rooms without aggroing mobs from the water.  these rooms have 2 spawns each with a few single spawns inbetween the rooms.  Icy/Watery are semi-rare spawns here and we never saw a shimmering mob.<br>
<br>
After a few hours camping I got an itch and started to explore the air/land tunnel above the water channel.  I found a path leading North, makes 2 180s and continnues north to a bridge and a castle.   In the north bound tunnel there were 2 rooms with only Icy/watery mobs.  First room (most southern) had 3 mobs and the room further north had 2 spawns.<br>
<br>
The second clearing of the 3 spawn room poped a shimmering mob with sword,  my wavecrasher.<br>
<br>
Based on my experience you need a spot that only spawns Icy/Waterys ie Castle area, tunnels i meantioned, or a similar place around the sirens.<br>
